f British, European, and American art and design. Bradstreet’s rich analyses of paintings, perfume posters, and other works of visual culture demonstrate how artworks mirrored the “period nose” and intersected with the most clamorous debates of the day, including evolution, civilization, race, urban morality, mental health, faith, and the “woman question.”Beautifully illustrated and grounded in current practices in sensory history, Scented Visions presents both fresh readings of major works of art and a deeper understanding of the cultural history of nineteenth-century scent.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aART / History / Modern (late 19th Century to 1945).2bisacsh  aAestheticism.  aCultural history of smell.  aDecadence.  aGeorge Frederick Watts.  aJohn Singer Sargent.  aMiasma.  aMillais.  aNineteenth-century painting.  aOdor / Odour.  aOlfactory.  aPerfume.  aPre-Raphaelitism.  aRossetti.  aScent.  aSensory history.  aSimeon Solomon.  aSmell.  aSynaesthesia.  aVictorian art .  aVictorian painting.  aVictorian studies.  aWaterhouse.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2022z9783110992809oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2022 Englishz978311099281608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978027109258440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271092584423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780271092584/original  a978-3-11-099281-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA